modules.description: Parses Tailwind CSS selectors from a lexing buffer, converting them into structured data. It handles low-level lexing and error reporting, producing optional selector values or detailed parsing results. Useful for integrating Tailwind CSS class parsing into build tools or linters that require precise source location tracking and class analysis.

This module parses and processes Tailwind CSS selectors, converting them into structured data for analysis or code generation. It works with strings, lexing buffers, and Tailwind-specific data structures, supporting operations like selector expansion and rule application. It is used to build Tailwind-aware tools such as linters, formatters, or PPX extensions that transform class names into optimized CSS or OCaml expressions.
